-- Warriors’ Lee Back in Uniform, Could Play Tonight Versus Denver
-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 2013-05-03T02:28:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-03/warriors-lee-back-in-uniform-could-play-tonight-versus-denver.html
All-Star forward David Lee is in
uniform for the Golden State Warriors tonight and could play for
the first time since hurting his hip in the first game of the
team’s playoff series against the  Denver Nuggets .  The Warriors lead the National Basketball Association
first-round series three games to two against the Nuggets and
can move on to the second round against the San Antonio Spurs
with a win tonight at home.   Lee, 30, is in his third season with the Warriors after
spending his first five NBA seasons with the  New York Knicks .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Gloster at 
 rgloster@bloomberg.net  